  "content_markdown": "Version: 8.2All Creatio products\nOn this page\nThis app is available in Sales, Marketing, and Service Creatio products.\nUse the **Customer 360** app to create and maintain extensive databases of contacts and accounts that are accessible easily at any time. **Contacts** in Creatio are individuals that are customers, partners, clients, employees, and other business connections. **Accounts** are companies that are customers, partners, contractors, suppliers, competitors, and other business entities.\nCreatio maintains the integrity and relevance of your datasets by regularly identifying and merging duplicate contact and account profiles. You can also search for duplicates manually. Learn more: [Find and merge duplicates](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=1591).\nIf you have the **Customer 360** app installed, Freedom UI Designer will have new components you can use in your own customizations:\n* **Contact compact profile**. Displays main data of a contact.\n* **Account compact profile**. Displays main data of an account.\n* **Communication options**. Lets you manage communication options of a record.\nYou can customize the **Customer 360** app similar to any Freedom UI app to make sure it fits your business goals as closely as possible.\n## Sections\u200b\nnote\nAvailable sections and their business logic might differ if you have other composable apps installed. Learn more: [Customer 360 enhancements by other Creatio apps](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=2488).\nCustomer 360 app includes **Contacts** and **Accounts** sections out of the box.\nUse the **Contacts** section to manage information about contacts, group them by various parameters, and analyze the history of interactions with contacts. The contact form page includes personal information, socio-demographic data, communication options, preferred communication channels, timeline, attachments, and feed.\nFig. 1 Contact form page\n![Fig.\u00a01 Contact form page](https://academy.creatio.com/docs/sites/en/files/images/CRM_Tools/customer_360_overview/scr_contact.png)\nUse the **Accounts** section to manage information about accounts, group them by various parameters, track relationships among accounts and contacts, and analyze the history of interactions with accounts. The account form page includes company details, categories, socio-demographic data, banking details, contact persons, corporate structure, communication options, preferred communication channels, timeline, attachments, and feed.\nFig. 2 Account form page\n![Fig.\u00a02 Account form page](https://academy.creatio.com/docs/sites/en/files/images/CRM_Tools/customer_360_overview/scr_account.png)\n## Tools\u200b\nCustomer 360 app includes various tools that streamline contact and account management:\n* Record filters. Learn more: [Filters](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=1017).\n* Record tags. Learn more: [Tags](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=1881).\n* Contact and account relationship chart. Learn more: [Add relationships between accounts and contacts](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=1315).\n* Search for record duplicates configured out of the box. Learn more: [Find and merge duplicates](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=1591).\n* * *\n## See also\u200b\n[Customer 360 enhancements by other Creatio apps](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=2488)\n[Customer 360 enhancements by other Creatio apps](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=2488)\n[Create contact](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=1002)\n[Enrich contact data](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=1733)\n[Manage job experience](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=2161)\n[Manage communication options and addresses](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=1309)\n[Calculate contact age](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=2046)",
